<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q31_v5" title="Q31_v5" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceD</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float"><qti-default-value><qti-value>0</qti-value></qti-default-value></qti-outcome-declaration><qti-item-body>
    <p>En una promoción de una pizzería se compran tres pizzas familiares y tres pizzas individuales, gastándose en total $23&#160;280.</p>
    <p>Cada pizza individual cuesta $390 menos que una pizza familiar. ¿Cuál de las siguientes ecuaciones permite determinar el precio <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math> de una pizza familiar, en pesos?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" max-choices="1">
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        <m:math>
          <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>390</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>23&#160;280</m:mn>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Esta ecuación solo considera 3 pizzas familiares y luego suma 390 una vez, pero el problema habla de 3 pizzas familiares y 3 individuales. Si <strong>x = 4075</strong>, que sí satisface la situación real, entonces <strong>3 × 4075 + 390 = 12&#160;225 + 390 = 12&#160;615</strong>, y <strong>12&#160;615 ≠ 23&#160;280</strong>. Por eso esta ecuación no representa el problema.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        <m:math>
          <m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>390</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>23&#160;280</m:mn>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Esta ecuación descuenta 390 solo una vez, pero hay 3 pizzas individuales, así que el descuento total debe ser <strong>3 × 390 = 1170</strong>. Si <strong>x = 4075</strong>, entonces <strong>6 × 4075 − 390 = 24&#160;450 − 390 = 24&#160;060</strong>, y <strong>24&#160;060 ≠ 23&#160;280</strong>. Por eso esta ecuación no satisface el problema.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        <m:math>
          <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>390</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>23&#160;280</m:mn>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Aquí la pizza individual queda con precio <strong>x + 390</strong>, pero el enunciado dice que cuesta <strong>390 menos</strong>, es decir, <strong>x − 390</strong>. Si <strong>x = 4075</strong>, entonces <strong>3 × 4075 + 3 × (4075 + 390) = 12&#160;225 + 3 × 4465 = 12&#160;225 + 13&#160;395 = 25&#160;620</strong>, y <strong>25&#160;620 ≠ 23&#160;280</strong>. Por eso esta ecuación no corresponde.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        <m:math>
          <m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>390</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>23&#160;280</m:mn>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Las 3 pizzas familiares aportan <strong>3x</strong> y las 3 individuales aportan <strong>3(x − 390)</strong>, porque cada individual vale 390 menos que una familiar. Entonces la suma correcta es <strong>3x + 3(x − 390) = 23&#160;280</strong>. Al resolver, <strong>3x + 3x − 1170 = 23&#160;280</strong>, luego <strong>6x = 24&#160;450</strong> y <strong>x = 4075</strong>. Verificación: <strong>3 × 4075 + 3 × 3685 = 12&#160;225 + 11&#160;055 = 23&#160;280</strong>.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Definir la variable</strong></p>
            <p>Sea <m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math> el precio de una pizza familiar, en pesos.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Expresar el precio de una pizza individual</strong></p>
            <p>Como cada pizza individual cuesta $390 menos que una pizza familiar, su precio es:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>390</m:mn></m:math></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Representar el costo total de las 6 pizzas</strong></p>
            <p>Tres pizzas familiares cuestan:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi></m:math></p>
            <p>Tres pizzas individuales cuestan:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>390</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:math></p>
            <p>Como en total se gastan $23&#160;280, la ecuación es:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>390</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>23&#160;280</m:mn></m:math></p>
            <p>Esta corresponde a la alternativa <strong>D</strong>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Resolver la ecuación</strong></p>
            <p>Desarrollamos:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1170</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>23&#160;280</m:mn></m:math></p>
            <p>Reducimos términos semejantes:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1170</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>23&#160;280</m:mn></m:math></p>
            <p>Sumamos 1170 en ambos lados:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>24&#160;450</m:mn></m:math></p>
            <p>Dividimos por 6:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>4075</m:mn></m:math></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Verificar el resultado</strong></p>
            <p>Precio de una pizza familiar:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mn>4075</m:mn></m:math></p>
            <p>Precio de una pizza individual:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mn>4075</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>390</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>3685</m:mn></m:math></p>
            <p>Costo de 3 familiares:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>4075</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>12&#160;225</m:mn></m:math></p>
            <p>Costo de 3 individuales:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>×</m:mo><m:mn>3685</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>11&#160;055</m:mn></m:math></p>
            <p>Suma total:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mn>12&#160;225</m:mn><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>11&#160;055</m:mn><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>23&#160;280</m:mn></m:math></p>
            <p>La verificación coincide con el enunciado.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La ecuación que permite determinar el precio de una pizza familiar es:</p>
            <p><m:math><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mi>x</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>390</m:mn><m:mo>)</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>23&#160;280</m:mn></m:math></p>
            <p>Por lo tanto, la alternativa correcta es <strong>D</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            ChoiceD
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            FB_ChoiceD
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            show
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            ChoiceA
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            FB_ChoiceA
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            show
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            ChoiceB
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            FB_ChoiceB
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            show
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            ChoiceC
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            FB_ChoiceC
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            show
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            FB_ChoiceA
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">
            show
          </qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>